The Policy Lab presented the MImPG project at the "Creative & Scientific Festival: Transforming
Public Action," which took place on April 22 and 23, 2026, at Usquare in Brussels. The festival
aimed to bring together researchers and practitioners from various fields who are working to 
improve public services and policies through not only scientific but also creative approaches
to transform public action, as the title suggests.

In this context, we had two opportunities to present our research and our project. In our first
presentation, we discussed the transdisciplinary nature of our project, our methodological approach,
as well as the challenges and opportunities involved in establishing a dialogue between technological
developments and stakeholders’ daily practices. In our second presentation, we shared our first 
serious game, which is designed to establish this dialogue through a creative approach. 

Over the next few months, we plan to further develop our game-based methodologies and identify 
strategies for a more sustainable internet in Brussels.
